      "writtenOn": "2019-04-04T23:05:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "then the user can explicitly pass in -json.\n\nI think the use case for bb | bb is more common and prone to people forgetting to pass in a magical flag that is required to make it work.\n\nCurrently there are no cases where \"bb (without -id) | anything\" should be valid.  Defaulting to detection (with override maybe, like -summary) will make it work by default for 1 out of the 2 known cases, which I think is better than 0 out of the 2 known cases.",
