      "writtenOn": "2019-04-05T02:32:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I think the use case for bb | bb is more common and prone to people forgetting to pass in a magical flag that is required to make it work.\n\nwhy do you think so? There is only use case for using -id right now: massive cancelation. This will be used only in outages. \n\non the other hand, -json is for any ad-hoc jq-based queries. I expect this to be used much more often. David actually reached out to me that he is excited about this tool being jq-friendly.\n\n\u003e Currently there are no cases where \"bb (without -id) | anything\" should be valid. \n\nI disagree.\n\n  bb -json | jq\n\nis valid and it does not have -id.\n\nI often use\n\n  bb something | less\n\nI wouldn\u0027t want to see json there.",
      "parentUuid": "b5198be2_f52e6663",
      "revId": "203eb608c9fc0c7a49fd2ff506311d3a97dd676b",
