        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-04T00:18:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is a bit confusing.  I don\u0027t think we gain much from making stdin reading concurrently.  It would be much simpler to resolve all args first and then start working.  I don\u0027t think most utilities that read from stdin start doing work until the stdin is closed.\n\nled does it\nhttps://cs.chromium.org/chromium/infra/go/src/infra/tools/led/cmd_edit.go?sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026dr\u0026q\u003dstdin+file:%5Einfra/go/src/infra/tools/led/+package:%5Echromium$\u0026g\u003d0\u0026l\u003d107",
      "revId": "203eb608c9fc0c7a49fd2ff506311d3a97dd676b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3458ad92_a3f27407",
        "filename": "buildbucket/cli/printrun.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 205,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-04T18:02:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i don\u0027t think so. Try:\n\n  yes | xargs echo\n  yes | grep y\n\njq has a special flag to enable buffering --slurp\n\nby default tools do not buffer stdin. This would be very inefficient. Imagine catting hundreds of files into grep.\n\nIf this code is removed, then `bb ls -id | bb cancel` would not start canceling builds until ls finishes completely. This would be undesierable.",
      "parentUuid": "adae2bd0_f8b14b2f",
      "revId": "203eb608c9fc0c7a49fd2ff506311d3a97dd676b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2b8d1509_52c56ceb",
        "filename": "buildbucket/cli/printrun.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 205,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-04T23:05:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In theory if bb is meant to cancel an unbounded amount of data like xargs or grep, I think this would make sense.\nBut ls is synchronous - It makes 1 request and all of it is printed at once, so a concurrent processing pipeline actually doesn\u0027t buy us any gains.\nThis would be more useful if ls was paged.  But I noticed there is a TODO in ls, so maybe this will be useful one day.\n\nI think this pipeline is clever, but it took me 10-15 min to read, and I expect it would take future readers about the same amount of time, and I think that is the main cost.  It would be good to make sure this complexity is well justified.",
      "parentUuid": "3458ad92_a3f27407",
      "revId": "203eb608c9fc0c7a49fd2ff506311d3a97dd676b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f675bce4_f0594f78",
        "filename": "buildbucket/cli/printrun.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 205,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-05T02:32:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the justification is mitigation of outages when we need to cancel a lot of builds. +Ben Pastene can tell you more about this if justification is unclear.\n\nAlso this is meant to close crbug.com/747322 and replace delete_many_builds API. Its is existence is clearly justified because we relied on it a few times.",
      "parentUuid": "2b8d1509_52c56ceb",
      "revId": "203eb608c9fc0c7a49fd2ff506311d3a97dd676b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
